"56:73:4" : {s: 56, a: 73, w: 4, r: "متع", t: "وَمَتَٰعًۭا", l: "مَتَٰع", lc: 35, tl: "wamatāʿan", lb: "জীবিকা, ভোগ্যবস্তু, আসবাবপত্র",e: "and a provision", b: "ভোগ্যসামগ্রী", f: 3, rm: "to enjoy/benefit, gift, anything useful/advantageous, goods (e.g. utensils, furniture), a commodity."},
"56:73:5" : {s: 56, a: 73, w: 5, r: "قوي", t: "لِّلْمُقْوِينَ", l: "مُقْوِين", lc: 1, tl: "lil'muq'wīna", lb: "নির্জন মরুবাসী",e: "for the wayfarers in the desert", b: "মরুবাসীদের জন্য", f: 1, rm: "to be, become strong, prevail, be able to do, be powerful, be vigorous, be forceful. quwwatun (pl. quwan) - power, strength, vigour, resolution, firmness, determination. qawun - desert. aqwa - to stay in desert. muqwin - dwellers of desert/wilderness (it is derived from the verb qawiya which means: it became desolate or deserted)."},
"56:74:1" : {s: 56, a: 74, w: 1, r: "سبح", t: "فَسَبِّحْ", l: "سَبَّحَ", lc: 42, tl: "fasabbiḥ", lb: "গুণকীর্তণ করা, পবিত্রতা ঘোষণা করা, তাসবীহ পাঠ করা",e: "So glorify", b: "পবিত্রতা বর্ণনা কর", f: 6, rm: ""},
"56:74:2" : {s: 56, a: 74, w: 2, r: "سمو", t: "بِٱسْمِ", l: "ٱسْم", lc: 151, tl: "bi-is'mi", lb: "নাম ",e: "(the) name", b: "নামে", f: 4, rm: ""},
"56:74:3" : {s: 56, a: 74, w: 3, r: "ربب", t: "رَبِّكَ", l: "رَبّ", lc: 975, tl: "rabbika", lb: "প্রভু, সযত্নে পালনকর্তা ",e: "(of) your Lord", b: "তোমার প্রভুর", f: 81, rm: "to be a lord and master, collect, possess/owner, rule, increase, complete, bring up, preserve, chief, guardian, regulator, determiner, caretaker, provider, sustainer, perfecter, rewarder, creator, maintainer, reposer of properties, developer, former of rules and laws of the growth, foster a thing in such a manner as to make it attain one condition after another until it reaches its goal of completion, the bringing a thing to a state of completion by degrees, whoever possesses a thing is its rabb."},
"56:74:4" : {s: 56, a: 74, w: 4, r: "عظم", t: "ٱلْعَظِيمِ", l: "عَظِيم", lc: 120, tl: "l-ʿaẓīmi", lb: "প্রচন্ড",e: "the Most Great", b: "মহান", f: 19, rm: "great, important, big, regard, honour, mighty, glorious, a man of moment, All-mighty, All-glorious, grievous, bounty/abounding, magnify/increase. azzama - to make great."},
"56:75:1" : {s: 56, a: 75, w: 1, r: "", t: "فَلَآ", l: "لَا", lc: 1738, tl: "Fala", lb: "না",e: "But nay,", b: "অতএব না", f: 156, rm: ""},
"56:75:2" : {s: 56, a: 75, w: 2, r: "قسم", t: "أُقْسِمُ", l: "أَقْسَمُ", lc: 20, tl: "uq'simu", lb: "শপথ করা",e: "I swear", b: "শপথ করছি", f: 8, rm: "to divide, dispose, separate, apportion, distribute. qasamun - oath. qismatun - partition, division, dividing, apportionment. maqsumun - divided/distinct. muqassimun (vb. 2) - one who takes oath, who apportions. qasama (vb. 3) - to swear. aqsama (vb. 4) - to swear. taqasama (vb. 6) - to swear one to another. muqtasimun (vb. 8) - who divides. istaqsama (vb. 10) - to draw lots. tastaqsimu - you seek division."},
"56:75:3" : {s: 56, a: 75, w: 3, r: "وقع", t: "بِمَوَٰقِعِ", l: "مَوَٰقِع", lc: 1, tl: "bimawāqiʿi", lb: "স্থান সমূহ",e: "by setting", b: "পতনস্থলসমূহের", f: 1, rm: "to fall down, befall, come to pass, be conformed, happen, take place, ascertain."},
"56:75:4" : {s: 56, a: 75, w: 4, r: "نجم", t: "ٱلنُّجُومِ", l: "نَّجْم", lc: 13, tl: "l-nujūmi", lb: "তারকারাজি",e: "(of) the stars", b: "তারকারাজি", f: 3, rm: "to appear/rise/begin, accomplish, ensue, proceed."},
"56:76:1" : {s: 56, a: 76, w: 1, r: "", t: "وَإِنَّهُۥ", l: "إِنّ", lc: 1536, tl: "Wainnahu", lb: "(জোর দিয়ে বলা) অবশ্যই, নিসন্দেহে",e: "And indeed, it", b: "এবং সে নিশ্চই (হবে)", f: 24, rm: ""},
"56:76:2" : {s: 56, a: 76, w: 2, r: "قسم", t: "لَقَسَمٌۭ", l: "قَسَم", lc: 2, tl: "laqasamun", lb: "শপথ",e: "(is) surely an oath", b: "শপথ", f: 1, rm: "to divide, dispose, separate, apportion, distribute. qasamun - oath. qismatun - partition, division, dividing, apportionment. maqsumun - divided/distinct. muqassimun (vb. 2) - one who takes oath, who apportions. qasama (vb. 3) - to swear. aqsama (vb. 4) - to swear. taqasama (vb. 6) - to swear one to another. muqtasimun (vb. 8) - who divides. istaqsama (vb. 10) - to draw lots. tastaqsimu - you seek division."},
"56:76:3" : {s: 56, a: 76, w: 3, r: "", t: "لَّوْ", l: "لَو", lc: 201, tl: "law", lb: "যদি হতো, যদি কিনা (অতীত)",e: "if", b: "যদি", f: 18, rm: ""},
"56:76:4" : {s: 56, a: 76, w: 4, r: "علم", t: "تَعْلَمُونَ", l: "عَلِمَ", lc: 382, tl: "taʿlamūna", lb: "(সে) জানে ",e: "you know", b: "জানো", f: 54, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows."},
"56:76:5" : {s: 56, a: 76, w: 5, r: "عظم", t: "عَظِيمٌ", l: "عَظِيم", lc: 120, tl: "ʿaẓīmun", lb: "প্রচন্ড",e: "great", b: "কঠিন", f: 31, rm: "great, important, big, regard, honour, mighty, glorious, a man of moment, All-mighty, All-glorious, grievous, bounty/abounding, magnify/increase. azzama - to make great."},
